verages was often depicted in Polish, Russian and Jewish literature of the 19th century, but the real knowledge about the East European rural Jews beyond the stereotypical view is still at large.The book presents the results of a systematic survey, the first of its kind, on the rural Jews in the Minsk Guberniya, from its establishment as a major administrative unit within the Russian Empire in 1793, to the outbreak of the First World War in 1914. The present study is based mainly on systematic sources, which produced, for the first time, a full picture of Jewish settlement in the countryside in one particular region of the Russian Empire.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aJewszEurope, EasternxHistoryy18th century. 0aJewszEurope, EasternxHistoryy19th century. 0aJewszEurope, EasternxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aBelarus, culture, demography, family structure, genealogy, Jews, landlords,.0 cEPUBz97831105762830 cprintz978311057601640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110576092zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110576092zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110576092.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA